.TH "TAKO" "1" "Jun 2026" "Tako CLI" "Tako CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
tako-access - Stream proxy access logs


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBtako access [service] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Stream and format access logs from tako-proxy.

.PP
This command shows HTTP request logs including:
  - Timestamp
  - HTTP status code (color-coded)
  - HTTP method
  - Client IP address
  - Response time
  - Response size
  - Request path

.PP
Similar to Vercel or Cloudflare observability, but for your own infrastructure.

.PP
Examples:
  tako access              # Show recent logs from the environment mesh
  tako access -f           # Follow logs in real-time
  tako access web          # Show logs for 'web' service
  tako access --server prod # Show logs from a specific node
  tako access --tail 50    # Show last 50 log entries
  tako access -v           # Verbose mode (includes User-Agent, Referer)


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-f\fP, \fB--follow\fP[=false]
	Follow log output

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for access

.PP
\fB-s\fP, \fB--server\fP=""
	Node to fetch logs from (default: all environment nodes)

.PP
\fB-n\fP, \fB--tail\fP=50
	Number of lines to show from the end


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--config\fP=""
	config file (default is ./tako.yaml or ./tako.json)

.PP
\fB-e\fP, \fB--env\fP=""
	environment to deploy (default: production or only environment)

.PP
\fB--events\fP=""
	stream progress events to stdout: ndjson (human output moves to stderr)

.PP
\fB--host-key-mode\fP=""
	SSH host key verification mode: tofu, strict, ask (default: tofu)

.PP
\fB--output\fP="text"
	output format: text or json (json reserves stdout for the final result document)

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=false]
	verbose output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBtako(1)\fP
